dataIdInfo.idPurp: CPAD dataset queried for city park locations. CPAD is suitable for a wide range of planning, assessment, analysis and display purposes. CPAD should not be used as the basis for regulatory, legal or other specific governmental actions. See the CPAD Data Disclaimer for more information. Clipped to Delta.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: The California Protected Areas Database (CPAD) contains data on lands owned in fee by governments, non-profits and some private entities that are protected for open space purposes. Data includes all such areas in California, from small urban parks to large national parks and forests, mostly aligned to assessor parcel boundaries. Data is collected by Holdings (parcels) which are aggregated to Units (commonly named areas within counties) and Super Units (commonly named areas generally).
dataIdInfo.idCredit: California Protected Areas Database (CPAD - www.calands.org). June 2019.

attr.attrdef: Open Access, Restricted, No Public Access. “Restricted Access” is limited (permit required, days/hours limited, etc.)."Open Access" means open to the public for agency-designated use.
Name of the SUPER UNIT/ Park
Unique ID for the SUPER UNIT. "NMA" refers to Name, Access, Manager - the three fields on which SUPER UNITS are based.
Jurisdiction level of managing agency: City, County, Federal, Non Profit, Private, Special District, State

Subtypes for Agency Levels: FEDERAL: Federal Agency; STATE: State Agency; COUNTY: County Agency, County Agency - Other, County Agency - Parks; CITY: City, City - Other Agency; SPECIAL DISTRICT: Transportation Agency, Airport District, Cemetery District, Community Services District, Fire District, Flood District, Irrigation District, Metropolitan Planning Organization, Open Space District, Port/Harbor District, Recreation/Parks District, Regional Park District, Sanitation District, School District, Special District - Other, Water District; NON PROFIT: Non Profit - Conservation, Non Profit - Other; PRIVATE: Private - Other; UNKNOWN: Unknown
Agency classifications used for symbology, based on State of California conventions
Abbreviated Name for cartographic labeling (e.g. “Sequoia NP”)
Year the park or management unit was formed. This field is defined at the Super Unit level and carried down to the Unit and Holding level. Date field in YYYY format.
